  "methodology": "Replicated S414 five-pattern detection (cascade, n1_inflation, silent, citation_loop, echo) on 849-lesson corpus. Genesis-era lessons (L-001..L-119, no Session: field) assigned estimated session numbers via linear interpolation from known lesson-num-to-session-num mapping (186 estimated, 0 still unknown). For each pattern type, extracted or estimated session number. Computed 4 temporal metrics: (1) Session distribution (min, max, median, IQR), (2) Burstiness via CV of inter-session gaps (CV>1=bursty, CV~1=Poisson, CV<1=regular), (3) Growth rate per 100 sessions in 5 eras, (4) Temporal co-occurrence via pairwise Jaccard on session sets. Note: pattern counts differ slightly from S414 (87 vs 128 n1_inflation) due to corpus growth (849 vs 835 lessons) and narrower implicit detection (S414 likely used broader matching for Theorized/Assumed confidence).",
  "hypothesis": "H1: Contamination patterns are temporally clustered (bursty, CV>1), not uniformly distributed. H2: Cascade growth rate accelerates with corpus size. H3: Citation loops concentrate in genesis era (S1-S100). H4: Patterns co-occur in the same sessions at above-chance rates.",
